
'''= CycleStreets Photomap - cycle infrastructure examples from around the world".'''

URL = http://www.cyclestreets.net/photomap/

=Description=

"The CycleStreets Photomap is a user-generated resource containing over 56,000 images of bicycle-related infrastructure from around the world, for the purposes of cycling advocacy.

The Photomap is part of a platform being built by CycleStreets which includes a cycle journey planner (using OpenStreetMap), opt-in GPS tracking, collision data viewing, and more."

=More Information=


All locations are fully-categorised, and contain metadata such as type, good/bad, location, captions, keywords (tags), time & date:
http://www.cyclestreets.net/photos/categories/

An API for third-party use is available:
http://www.cyclestreets.net/api/v2/

It can also be used as the basis for tools for cycle infrastructure audit, e.g.
http://www.urbancycleparking.org.uk/
which uses the same data interface (API).


